{
  "document_id": "job-36",
  "title": "Job 36",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-heading-elihu-exalts-god’s-g",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Elihu Exalts God’s Goodness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Elihu continued and said:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Bear with me a little, and I will show you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "I will bring my knowledge from far away"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "For truly my words are not false;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "“Surely God is mighty and does not despise any;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "He does not keep the wicked alive"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "He does not withdraw his eyes from the righteous,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "And if they are bound in fetters"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "then he declares to them their work"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "He opens their ears to instruction"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "If they listen and serve him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "But if they do not listen, they shall perish by the sword"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "“The godless in heart cherish anger;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "They die in their youth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "He delivers the afflicted by their affliction"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "He also allured you out of distress"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "“But you are obsessed with the case of the wicked;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Beware that wrath does not entice you into scoffing,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "Will your cry avail to keep you from distress,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Do not long for the night,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Beware! Do not turn to iniquity;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "See, God is exalted in his power;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Who has prescribed for him his way,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "“Remember to extol his work,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "All people have looked on it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Surely God is great, and we do not know him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "For he draws up the drops of water;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "which the skies pour down"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Can anyone understand the spreading of the clouds,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "See, he scatters his lightning around him"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "For by these he governs peoples;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "He covers his hands with the lightning"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-36-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "Its crashing tells about him;"
    }
  ]
}